cs.DM, cs.SI, cs.GT, cs.NA, cs.CE

Reasoning: 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a discrete-time stochastic process on graphs.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the Moran process is often used to model the spread of mutations in populations, which can be applied to social networks.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the behaviour of the Moran process on directed graphs, which can be modelled as a game between two players.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is relevant as the paper uses stochastic dominations to obtain bounds on the expected absorption time.
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is less likely but still possible as the Moran process has applications in computational biology and genetics.
